OL,3,CWhat is a shallow earthquake and why
OL,4,Care they so dangerous?
OL,6,FThe Richter Scale measures the
OL,7,Fmagnitude of earthquakes from 0 to 10,
OL,8,Fincreasing by 10-fold each time.
OL,10,FScientists used the Richter Scale for
OL,11,Fmany years but now largely follow the
OL,12,FModified Mercalli Intensity Scale,
OL,13,Fwhich the US Geological Survey says is
OL,14,Fa more accurate measure of size.
OL,16,FThe Richter scale measures magnitude,
OL,17,Fwhereas the MMI scale measures
OL,18,Fintensity.
